<div1 type="trialAccount" id="t17670218-20">
               <interp inst="t17670218-20" type="collection" value="BAILEY"></interp>
               <interp inst="t17670218-20" type="year" value="1767"></interp>
               <interp inst="t17670218-20" type="uri" value="sessionsPapers/17670218"></interp>
               <interp inst="t17670218-20" type="date" value="17670218"></interp>
               <join result="criminalCharge" id="t17670218-20-off111-c142" targOrder="Y" targets="t17670218-20-defend175 t17670218-20-off111 t17670218-20-verdict115"></join>
         
               <p>150. (L.) 
               
                  <persName id="t17670218-20-defend175" type="defendantName">
                     John 
                     Hasker 
                  <interp inst="t17670218-20-defend175" type="surname" value="Hasker"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17670218-20-defend175" type="given" value="John"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17670218-20-defend175" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
               
             was indicted for <rs id="t17670218-20-off111" type="offenceDescription">
                     <interp inst="t17670218-20-off111" type="offenceCategory" value="theft"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17670218-20-off111" type="offenceSubcategory" value="grandLarceny"></interp>
               stealing a linen shirt, value 7 s.
            </rs> the property of 
               
                  <persName id="t17670218-20-victim177" type="victimName">
                     James 
                     Williamson 
                  <interp inst="t17670218-20-victim177" type="surname" value="Williamson"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17670218-20-victim177" type="given" value="James"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17670218-20-victim177" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                     <join result="offenceVictim" targOrder="Y" targets="t17670218-20-off111 t17670218-20-victim177"></join>
                  </persName>
                
            , <rs id="t17670218-20-cd112" type="crimeDate">Feb. 10</rs>
                  <join result="offenceCrimeDate" targOrder="Y" targets="t17670218-20-off111 t17670218-20-cd112"></join>. ++</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t17670218-20-person178">
                  Elizabeth 
                  Williamson 
               <interp inst="t17670218-20-person178" type="surname" value="Williamson"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17670218-20-person178" type="given" value="Elizabeth"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17670218-20-person178" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am wife to 
               <persName id="t17670218-20-person179">
                  James 
                  Williamson 
               <interp inst="t17670218-20-person179" type="surname" value="Williamson"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17670218-20-person179" type="given" value="James"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17670218-20-person179" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            ; we <rs id="t17670218-20-viclabel113" type="occupation">keep <placeName id="t17670218-20-crimeloc114">the Bull and Butcher in Smithfield</placeName>
                     <interp inst="t17670218-20-crimeloc114" type="placeName" value="the Bull and Butcher in Smithfield"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17670218-20-crimeloc114" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                     <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t17670218-20-off111 t17670218-20-crimeloc114"></join>
                  </rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t17670218-20-victim177 t17670218-20-viclabel113"></join>; I had been washing all day; the prisoner came in, and called for a pennyworth of beer; he drank it, and called for another, and after that a third, and changed a shilling to pay for them; I went into the tap room, and hung a wet shirt upon the horse, and bid the maid go and take her supper; she went into the tap-room and said, the shirt and man are gone; I ran out, and found the prisoner almost at the end of Hosier-lane; I took hold of him with one hand, and the shirt with the other, and brought him back; my husband got a constable; (the shirt produced and deposed to.)</p>
               <p>Prisoner's defence.</p>
               <p>I was in great necessity, almost starving and perishing on the earth; I do not deny the thing; I am within six weeks of 66 years of age.</p>
               <p>To his character.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t17670218-20-person180">
                  Richard 
                  Hewit 
               <interp inst="t17670218-20-person180" type="surname" value="Hewit"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17670218-20-person180" type="given" value="Richard"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17670218-20-person180" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I have known him about a dozen years, he is a cabinet-maker by trade; I never heard any harm by him; he kept a house opposite the church at Islington when I first knew him.</p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t17670218-20-verdict115" type="verdictDescription">
                     <interp inst="t17670218-20-verdict115" type="verdictCategory" value="guilty"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17670218-20-verdict115" type="verdictSubcategory" value="theftunder1s"></interp>
               Guilty 10 d.
            </rs> 
                  <rs id="t17670218-20-punish116" type="punishmentDescription">
                     <interp inst="t17670218-20-punish116" type="punishmentCategory" value="transport"></interp>
                     <join result="defendantPunishment" targOrder="Y" targets="t17670218-20-defend175 t17670218-20-punish116"></join>
               T
            </rs>.</p>
            </div1>
